1
00:00:17,440 --> 00:00:19,280
You and Xie Qing seem pretty close.

2
00:00:22,510 --> 00:00:25,480
She was my only friend in Britain.

3
00:00:30,960 --> 00:00:32,500
I didn't think you had any friends.

4
00:00:32,500 --> 00:00:33,620
=Cases Between Us=

5
00:00:33,640 --> 00:00:35,110
You seem to know her quite well.

6
00:00:36,400 --> 00:00:38,280
=Episode 12=
You even know she likes iced Coke.

7
00:00:41,280 --> 00:00:42,240
Not really.

8
00:00:47,240 --> 00:00:48,000
Do you know

9
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:48,790
what I like to eat?

10
00:00:52,020 --> 00:00:52,900
Zhajiangmian?

11
00:00:54,100 --> 00:00:54,820
Stir-fried tripe?

12
00:00:56,420 --> 00:00:56,780
Hotpot?

13
00:00:56,780 --> 00:00:57,488
Stop guessing.

14
00:01:02,380 --> 00:01:03,060
Never mind.

15
00:01:09,340 --> 00:01:09,900
Pull over.

16
00:01:26,780 --> 00:01:28,220
I'm not thirsty anymore.

17
00:01:31,540 --> 00:01:32,220
Drive.

18
00:01:46,016 --> 00:01:47,808
Can you finish two bottles by yourself?

19
00:02:05,780 --> 00:02:09,380
(The Vengeful Ghost of the Eight Alleys)

20
00:02:09,380 --> 00:02:11,540
How did they find out about this?

21
00:02:13,700 --> 00:02:14,340
Master Jin,

22
00:02:14,420 --> 00:02:17,860
I'm guessing it was one of the girls
who bought her freedom before.

23
00:02:18,020 --> 00:02:19,220
She must've been talking.

24
00:02:19,340 --> 00:02:22,540
She's got some nerve running her mouth.

25
00:02:23,060 --> 00:02:24,740
(Jin Bonan)
I heard

26
00:02:25,140 --> 00:02:27,540
Xia Jinshu has been getting close
to Reporter Han.

27
00:02:28,460 --> 00:02:29,940
No way, Master Jin.

28
00:02:30,020 --> 00:02:31,140
It couldn't be her.

29
00:02:31,300 --> 00:02:32,980
She's been with me for over ten years.

30
00:02:33,460 --> 00:02:34,700
She's an obedient one.

31
00:02:35,020 --> 00:02:36,420
She does whatever I tell her.

32
00:02:36,500 --> 00:02:37,860
It can't be her.

33
00:02:39,900 --> 00:02:40,400
Master Jin,

34
00:02:40,460 --> 00:02:41,740
Shengxiamei Hair Salon is closed.

35
00:02:41,936 --> 00:02:43,888
And the police want to
question Madam Feng.

36
00:02:47,940 --> 00:02:51,860
(Jingshi Police Department)

37
00:02:52,740 --> 00:02:53,860
- Chief Yuan.
- Chief Yuan.

38
00:02:53,860 --> 00:02:55,620
(Division Four)

39
00:02:55,620 --> 00:02:56,300
Chief,

40
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:58,176
the people at
the Handan Pleasure House said

41
00:02:58,192 --> 00:02:59,600
the girl named Xiaoman was released.

42
00:02:59,616 --> 00:03:00,380
I had no choice,

43
00:03:00,380 --> 00:03:01,900
so I brought Madam Feng in.

44
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:05,168
Right after you left yesterday,

45
00:03:05,184 --> 00:03:07,220
(Rid the People of Evil)
about fifteen minutes later,

46
00:03:07,220 --> 00:03:09,220
someone came and paid for her freedom.

47
00:03:10,060 --> 00:03:10,820
Who was it?

48
00:03:12,380 --> 00:03:13,900
A man in his forties.

49
00:03:13,968 --> 00:03:16,460
His clothes were filthy,
and his hands were covered in calluses.

50
00:03:16,496 --> 00:03:18,340
He said he was there
on his boss's orders.

51
00:03:20,540 --> 00:03:21,700
Was he driving a small truck?

52
00:03:22,540 --> 00:03:23,500
How did you know?

53
00:03:28,432 --> 00:03:29,740
Did you get the license plate?

54
00:03:30,380 --> 00:03:32,140
How would I remember that?

55
00:03:32,340 --> 00:03:33,500
I'm not a fortune teller.

56
00:03:35,900 --> 00:03:37,580
Xia Jinshu's one of you, isn't she?

57
00:03:38,688 --> 00:03:39,700
Let's talk about her.

58
00:03:39,940 --> 00:03:40,780
Tell us everything.

59
00:03:40,900 --> 00:03:42,260
Don't make things up.

60
00:03:42,260 --> 00:03:43,380
She's free now.

61
00:03:43,380 --> 00:03:44,900
She has nothing to do with us anymore.

62
00:03:46,380 --> 00:03:48,420
You're still denying it, huh?

63
00:03:48,420 --> 00:03:49,700
You think we're soft?

64
00:03:49,900 --> 00:03:50,580
Fine, fine.

65
00:03:50,780 --> 00:03:52,060
Whatever you say.

66
00:03:52,080 --> 00:03:53,460
I know where I am right now.

67
00:03:53,460 --> 00:03:54,820
The police department.

68
00:03:55,060 --> 00:03:56,140
I came here today

69
00:03:56,140 --> 00:03:58,260
not expecting to walk out in one piece.

70
00:03:58,260 --> 00:03:58,700
What?

71
00:03:58,700 --> 00:04:00,380
You think someone's coming
to bail you out?

72
00:04:01,380 --> 00:04:03,020
Who would bail me out?

73
00:04:03,220 --> 00:04:04,780
I'm just a brothel madam.

74
00:04:05,060 --> 00:04:06,820
I'll be lucky if I don't die in prison.

75
00:04:15,060 --> 00:04:16,500
If not in prison,

76
00:04:17,020 --> 00:04:18,740
then maybe you'll die outside instead.

77
00:04:21,100 --> 00:04:22,860
Don't jinx me.

78
00:04:29,940 --> 00:04:31,740
That man's boss

79
00:04:32,340 --> 00:04:34,300
has killed three people.

80
00:04:36,900 --> 00:04:38,100
Besides Lu Ruiheng,

81
00:04:38,540 --> 00:04:39,660
there are Huang Erya

82
00:04:39,940 --> 00:04:42,700
and her son.

83
00:04:45,180 --> 00:04:46,260
Think carefully.

84
00:04:47,420 --> 00:04:49,740
Who's next? Xia Jinshu?

85
00:04:50,860 --> 00:04:52,100
Or...

86
00:04:54,460 --> 00:04:55,340
you?

87
00:05:04,100 --> 00:05:05,260
Young Master Zhao,

88
00:05:05,700 --> 00:05:06,980
don't scare me like that.

89
00:05:07,180 --> 00:05:08,420
I've got a weak heart.

90
00:05:08,580 --> 00:05:09,460
I scare easily.

91
00:05:09,980 --> 00:05:11,820
If you want to stay alive,
cooperate with us.

92
00:05:12,060 --> 00:05:13,420
If you try to play games with me...

93
00:05:30,900 --> 00:05:34,140
(Rid the People of Evil)

94
00:06:00,260 --> 00:06:01,580
Master Jin.

95
00:06:03,460 --> 00:06:05,380
I've been in the Eight Alleys for years.

96
00:06:05,620 --> 00:06:06,540
I know the rules.

97
00:06:12,140 --> 00:06:13,860
Reporter Han came to me so many times.

98
00:06:14,260 --> 00:06:14,540
I...

99
00:06:14,540 --> 00:06:15,860
I never said a word.

100
00:06:15,860 --> 00:06:16,700
What about Qiao'er?

101
00:06:17,460 --> 00:06:18,580
Have you figured out

102
00:06:19,100 --> 00:06:20,060
who she was?

103
00:06:23,820 --> 00:06:26,100
Young girl, you came
to Beijing all by yourself?

104
00:06:27,460 --> 00:06:29,860
I want to make something of myself
before I go back home.

105
00:06:30,700 --> 00:06:31,860
I want to learn how to sing.

106
00:06:33,060 --> 00:06:34,180
You're pretty,

107
00:06:34,180 --> 00:06:35,460
and you've got a lovely voice.

108
00:06:35,460 --> 00:06:36,780
You'd make a great singer.

109
00:06:42,780 --> 00:06:43,460
There you go.

110
00:06:44,340 --> 00:06:45,020
Thank you.

111
00:06:45,550 --> 00:06:46,260
Come.

112
00:06:51,340 --> 00:06:53,700
(Mulian Hair Oil)

113
00:07:03,060 --> 00:07:03,620
Miss,

114
00:07:03,872 --> 00:07:05,408
the hair oil is excellent.

115
00:07:05,424 --> 00:07:06,850
(Mulian Hair Oil)
It smells nice too.

116
00:07:06,860 --> 00:07:08,460
I'm sure you need this product.

117
00:07:08,700 --> 00:07:11,060
Call the Beijing distributor.

118
00:07:11,152 --> 00:07:12,912
You can get it at 42 percent off retail.

119
00:07:13,100 --> 00:07:14,420
You know them?

120
00:07:14,580 --> 00:07:15,340
My...

121
00:07:15,830 --> 00:07:18,100
My family owns a general store.

122
00:07:18,192 --> 00:07:19,344
I know the wholesale price.

123
00:07:21,180 --> 00:07:22,460
Her family runs a general store?

124
00:07:26,860 --> 00:07:28,580
You couldn't even get
anything out of her.

125
00:07:28,580 --> 00:07:30,140
What good are you to me?

126
00:07:30,500 --> 00:07:31,700
Master Jin.

127
00:07:31,700 --> 00:07:33,140
I thought she was an innocent girl,

128
00:07:33,660 --> 00:07:35,060
so I didn't think much of it.

129
00:07:35,060 --> 00:07:36,860
She was able to cause this much trouble.

130
00:07:36,860 --> 00:07:38,816
Her family's got to have
some serious connections.

131
00:07:39,140 --> 00:07:39,900
Hit her.

132
00:07:39,900 --> 00:07:40,700
Master Jin!

133
00:07:43,420 --> 00:07:44,180
Master Jin!

134
00:07:45,540 --> 00:07:46,310
Master Jin!

135
00:07:46,320 --> 00:07:46,940
Come here.

136
00:07:47,104 --> 00:07:47,904
Master Jin.

137
00:07:47,952 --> 00:07:50,020
Prepare more silver coins
for the police department.

138
00:07:50,020 --> 00:07:51,380
If anyone starts looking into this,

139
00:07:51,380 --> 00:07:52,740
let them take the heat first.

140
00:07:52,740 --> 00:07:53,340
Yes.

141
00:07:54,060 --> 00:07:55,180
Master Jin.

142
00:07:59,420 --> 00:08:00,460
Goddess Guanyin.

143
00:08:00,900 --> 00:08:02,180
Goddess Guanyin, please bless me.

144
00:08:04,980 --> 00:08:05,900
Chief Yuan,

145
00:08:05,980 --> 00:08:07,500
it's getting late. Could I...

146
00:08:07,540 --> 00:08:09,690
We want to see the owner
of the Handan House, Jin Bonan.

147
00:08:09,700 --> 00:08:10,352
Where is he?

148
00:08:16,140 --> 00:08:17,460
He went to Xia Jinshu's house.

149
00:08:17,776 --> 00:08:19,136
What's he planning to do?

150
00:08:19,460 --> 00:08:19,820
He...

151
00:08:23,060 --> 00:08:24,140
He's gone to confront her.

152
00:08:27,980 --> 00:08:29,540
Wait, Chief Yuan. I...

153
00:08:37,340 --> 00:08:38,900
Wan'er just called.

154
00:08:39,408 --> 00:08:40,260
What did she say?

155
00:08:40,700 --> 00:08:41,900
Her friend in the northeast

156
00:08:41,900 --> 00:08:42,820
has seen Xie Fu.

157
00:08:43,220 --> 00:08:44,620
The sisters look almost identical.

158
00:08:44,620 --> 00:08:45,820
Except...

159
00:08:46,144 --> 00:08:48,060
the younger sister
is about a head shorter.

160
00:08:48,060 --> 00:08:48,700
Do you remember

161
00:08:48,700 --> 00:08:50,340
the girl standing by the door

162
00:08:50,340 --> 00:08:52,140
when we sent Xie Qing home?

163
00:08:53,424 --> 00:08:55,232
She was about the same height
as Xie Qing.

164
00:09:07,780 --> 00:09:10,220
Do you really know Xie Qing?

165
00:09:12,260 --> 00:09:13,820
What are you trying to say?

166
00:09:13,820 --> 00:09:15,060
If Xie Qing is the killer,

167
00:09:15,060 --> 00:09:16,220
what will you do?

168
00:09:26,820 --> 00:09:27,540
Qing.

169
00:09:36,020 --> 00:09:38,020
Mr. Li said Xia Jinshu
isn't at the shop.

170
00:09:38,020 --> 00:09:38,820
I'll go check.

171
00:09:40,940 --> 00:09:41,980
Would you kill her?

172
00:10:07,700 --> 00:10:08,380
Qing.

173
00:10:20,336 --> 00:10:21,800
Other than carbon monoxide poisoning,

174
00:10:21,820 --> 00:10:23,500
could Madam Huang and her son

175
00:10:23,940 --> 00:10:25,180
have died some other way?

176
00:10:26,740 --> 00:10:28,180
Could they have been suffocated?

177
00:10:30,300 --> 00:10:31,540
But the case file says

178
00:10:31,540 --> 00:10:33,020
there were no marks on their necks.

179
00:10:33,420 --> 00:10:34,580
Is there a way

180
00:10:35,340 --> 00:10:37,260
to suffocate someone

181
00:10:37,260 --> 00:10:40,300
without leaving any marks?

182
00:10:43,900 --> 00:10:44,780
A rear naked choke.

183
00:10:45,660 --> 00:10:47,660
It's mandatory training
at the military academy.

184
00:10:54,900 --> 00:10:56,700
Before Lu Ruiheng was hanged,

185
00:10:58,060 --> 00:10:59,900
that's probably what the killer used.

186
00:11:01,060 --> 00:11:02,780
(Mulian Hair Oil)

187
00:11:02,940 --> 00:11:06,100
(Xie's Cosmetic Factory)

188
00:11:06,860 --> 00:11:07,940
The Xie's Cosmetic Factory

189
00:11:07,940 --> 00:11:10,580
has plenty of trucks
at its Beijing distribution center,

190
00:11:10,580 --> 00:11:11,980
along with those tools.

191
00:11:11,980 --> 00:11:13,460
Do you remember the marks

192
00:11:13,460 --> 00:11:15,180
left by the pulleys on those branches?

193
00:11:15,380 --> 00:11:17,740
They look like
wilderness climbing knots.

194
00:11:17,740 --> 00:11:20,180
A lesson in Woolwich survival training.

195
00:11:20,180 --> 00:11:21,340
From Xiaoman

196
00:11:21,340 --> 00:11:23,300
driving Lu Ruiheng away that night

197
00:11:23,300 --> 00:11:25,060
to slipping me that paper,

198
00:11:25,500 --> 00:11:27,060
to leading the police to discover

199
00:11:27,060 --> 00:11:29,660
that Madam Huang and her son's deaths
weren't an accident,

200
00:11:29,940 --> 00:11:32,140
and then Xiaoman finding Han Zhenzhu

201
00:11:32,140 --> 00:11:33,712
and getting that article published...

202
00:11:39,220 --> 00:11:40,300
It was Xie Qing.

203
00:12:05,700 --> 00:12:06,180
Don't...

204
00:12:06,540 --> 00:12:07,540
Don't kill me.

205
00:12:09,100 --> 00:12:10,420
Don't kill me...

206
00:12:25,420 --> 00:12:26,900
You should've called the police.

207
00:12:27,900 --> 00:12:29,780
You think I never did?

208
00:12:31,140 --> 00:12:32,460
Those animals

209
00:12:33,860 --> 00:12:35,260
are still walking free today

210
00:12:35,872 --> 00:12:37,740
because they've got people
protecting them.

211
00:12:39,220 --> 00:12:41,420
My family has got money,

212
00:12:42,140 --> 00:12:43,740
but to people like them,

213
00:12:44,660 --> 00:12:46,460
we're nothing but ants.

214
00:12:51,020 --> 00:12:52,340
Now you have two options.

215
00:12:55,220 --> 00:12:56,460
Kill her

216
00:12:56,460 --> 00:12:57,580
and silence the witness,

217
00:12:58,740 --> 00:12:59,940
or turn yourself in.

218
00:13:01,660 --> 00:13:03,180
I'll find you the best lawyer.

219
00:13:04,780 --> 00:13:05,700
It's your choice.

220
00:13:10,900 --> 00:13:12,220
What do you think I should do?

221
00:13:12,780 --> 00:13:14,380
The choice is yours,

222
00:13:15,980 --> 00:13:16,940
not mine.

223
00:13:17,584 --> 00:13:18,860
If I choose the first one,

224
00:13:20,260 --> 00:13:21,460
you'll be guilty of misconduct.

225
00:13:22,300 --> 00:13:24,180
You'll never be able to be a cop again.

226
00:13:24,860 --> 00:13:25,980
If I turn myself in,

227
00:13:26,352 --> 00:13:27,700
you'll spend the rest of my life

228
00:13:27,700 --> 00:13:29,380
feeling guilty

229
00:13:29,728 --> 00:13:31,460
for putting me behind bars yourself.

230
00:13:36,140 --> 00:13:37,580
Neither choice is any good.

231
00:13:38,820 --> 00:13:39,940
Then what do you want to do?

232
00:13:45,940 --> 00:13:46,940
Kill her.

233
00:13:46,940 --> 00:13:47,940
Then you arrest me.

234
00:13:49,536 --> 00:13:51,584
She may be guilty,
but she doesn't deserve to die.

235
00:13:51,620 --> 00:13:52,620
You can't kill her.

236
00:13:52,620 --> 00:13:53,700
Say something.

237
00:13:55,820 --> 00:13:56,860
You can't stop me.

238
00:13:56,900 --> 00:13:59,200
I can't, but I have to.
She's just like those other girls.

239
00:13:59,216 --> 00:14:00,190
None of them had a choice.

240
00:14:00,200 --> 00:14:01,190
They were all just pawns.

241
00:14:01,200 --> 00:14:04,320
If you're capable, go after the people
pulling the strings behind all this...

242
00:14:08,224 --> 00:14:10,260
As long as I'm here,
you won't lay a finger on her.

243
00:14:10,260 --> 00:14:10,860
Yuan Hong!

244
00:14:10,860 --> 00:14:11,700
You frozen?

245
00:14:12,820 --> 00:14:13,780
Grab her!

246
00:14:28,128 --> 00:14:29,020
Give me your hand.

247
00:14:29,100 --> 00:14:29,980
Get up.

248
00:15:51,740 --> 00:15:53,340
What did my sister ever do wrong?

249
00:15:55,860 --> 00:16:00,420
(Employment Agency, Women Preferred)

250
00:16:00,860 --> 00:16:03,540
(Xie Fu)

251
00:16:09,260 --> 00:16:10,180
Young girl.

252
00:16:11,300 --> 00:16:12,820
You've got

253
00:16:12,820 --> 00:16:14,020
a great look.

254
00:16:14,300 --> 00:16:16,740
Ever thought about being a singer?
Or an actress?

255
00:16:17,940 --> 00:16:18,660
Me?

256
00:16:18,660 --> 00:16:20,020
Can I?

257
00:16:20,220 --> 00:16:21,420
Yeah.

258
00:16:21,700 --> 00:16:22,700
Of course.

259
00:16:22,700 --> 00:16:23,380
Come with me.

260
00:16:23,380 --> 00:16:23,900
Come on.

261
00:16:23,900 --> 00:16:26,780
(Employment Agency, Women Preferred)

262
00:16:26,780 --> 00:16:28,700
Have a seat.

263
00:16:28,940 --> 00:16:30,620
Let me see.

264
00:16:31,220 --> 00:16:33,220
How old are you?

265
00:16:33,900 --> 00:16:35,220
Seventeen.

266
00:16:39,180 --> 00:16:39,860
Madam Feng.

267
00:16:47,900 --> 00:16:48,500
Get up.

268
00:16:53,940 --> 00:16:54,860
Not bad.

269
00:16:54,860 --> 00:16:56,580
Such a pretty little face.

270
00:16:56,580 --> 00:16:57,940
She's still untouched.

271
00:16:57,940 --> 00:16:58,740
Madam Feng,

272
00:16:59,420 --> 00:17:00,420
find some rich fool

273
00:17:00,420 --> 00:17:02,140
and make a fortune off her.

274
00:17:06,940 --> 00:17:07,420
You...

275
00:17:08,380 --> 00:17:09,340
Who are you?

276
00:17:10,220 --> 00:17:11,500
Nice voice.

277
00:17:11,500 --> 00:17:12,940
Sounds like a little sparrow.

278
00:17:12,940 --> 00:17:13,620
Well,

279
00:17:13,620 --> 00:17:14,580
we'll call you Qiao'er.

280
00:17:14,900 --> 00:17:16,060
Where am I?

281
00:17:17,900 --> 00:17:19,620
Where is this?

282
00:17:21,180 --> 00:17:21,740
Come on.

283
00:17:21,740 --> 00:17:22,140
Everyone,

284
00:17:22,140 --> 00:17:24,100
let's congratulate Young Master Lu.

285
00:17:24,500 --> 00:17:25,820
Young Master Lu, come on.

286
00:17:25,820 --> 00:17:27,300
- Congratulations.
- Congratulations.

287
00:17:29,260 --> 00:17:29,780
Come on.

288
00:17:29,780 --> 00:17:30,820
Young Master Lu,

289
00:17:30,820 --> 00:17:32,260
you're lucky.

290
00:17:32,260 --> 00:17:33,860
You're the groom again.

291
00:17:33,860 --> 00:17:34,820
Right?

292
00:17:35,460 --> 00:17:36,700
With Madam Feng around,

293
00:17:36,700 --> 00:17:38,500
I've been a groom
more times than I can count.

294
00:17:38,704 --> 00:17:39,170
Of course.

295
00:17:39,180 --> 00:17:39,860
Not enough.

296
00:17:39,860 --> 00:17:41,020
I can never have too many.

297
00:17:41,620 --> 00:17:42,140
Come on.

298
00:17:42,140 --> 00:17:43,100
Eat up.

299
00:17:43,380 --> 00:17:45,100
The red flower looks nice.

300
00:17:49,100 --> 00:17:51,300
I almost forgot the important part,
Madam Feng.

301
00:17:51,300 --> 00:17:52,260
Come.

302
00:17:52,540 --> 00:17:53,500
Don't move.

303
00:17:54,820 --> 00:17:55,460
Qiao'er,

304
00:17:55,460 --> 00:17:56,580
they're all in the courtyard.

305
00:17:56,580 --> 00:17:57,620
You should run now.

306
00:17:58,620 --> 00:17:59,520
How?

307
00:17:59,800 --> 00:18:00,550
Come on.

308
00:18:00,810 --> 00:18:02,656
Every time I tried to run,
they beat me.

309
00:18:02,720 --> 00:18:03,700
Next time it'll be more.

310
00:18:03,700 --> 00:18:05,060
There's no way to get out of here.

311
00:18:06,870 --> 00:18:08,420
This is the only thing I have.

312
00:18:08,860 --> 00:18:09,700
I'm giving it to you.

313
00:18:15,500 --> 00:18:17,140
When my sister comes looking for me,

314
00:18:18,220 --> 00:18:19,980
give this to her.

315
00:18:20,700 --> 00:18:22,780
Beijing is so big.

316
00:18:23,140 --> 00:18:24,740
How could your sister ever find you?

317
00:18:25,100 --> 00:18:25,900
Trust me.

318
00:18:26,820 --> 00:18:27,860
She will.

319
00:18:31,980 --> 00:18:33,340
My name isn't Qiao'er.

320
00:18:34,220 --> 00:18:35,620
I'm Xie Fu.

321
00:18:47,300 --> 00:18:48,900
Beijing isn't beyond the law.

322
00:18:49,620 --> 00:18:50,500
Don't worry.

323
00:18:51,100 --> 00:18:52,660
I'll get justice for you.

324
00:18:53,780 --> 00:18:55,540
You're just a cop.

325
00:18:56,620 --> 00:18:57,540
They've all been

326
00:18:58,540 --> 00:19:00,420
working together for years.

327
00:19:01,480 --> 00:19:02,780
You can't beat them.

328
00:19:02,780 --> 00:19:04,860
How do you know
an ant can't bring down a tree?

329
00:19:05,620 --> 00:19:07,100
Those scum

330
00:19:07,380 --> 00:19:09,180
have been feeding on women.

331
00:19:10,100 --> 00:19:12,060
Even if it costs me my life,

332
00:19:12,380 --> 00:19:14,020
I'll fight them to the bitter end.

333
00:19:14,380 --> 00:19:17,940
(End of Episode 12)

334
00:19:19,561 --> 00:19:21,201
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

335
00:19:21,201 --> 00:19:22,741
♪Troubled times
are but a laughing matter♪

336
00:19:22,741 --> 00:19:23,991
♪However, the world changes♪

337
00:19:23,991 --> 00:19:25,911
♪You'll still be by my side♪

338
00:19:25,911 --> 00:19:27,601
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

339
00:19:27,601 --> 00:19:29,171
♪Praise and blame come and go♪

340
00:19:29,171 --> 00:19:30,741
♪If this is my final chapter♪

341
00:19:30,741 --> 00:19:33,241
♪I'll solve this mystery with you♪
